Class IntervalND

java.lang.Object
org.jscience.mathematics.algebra.intervals.IntervalND
All Implemented Interfaces:
Set<List<Real>>, TopologicalSpace<List<Real>>
public class IntervalND extends Object implements Set<List<Real>>, TopologicalSpace<List<Real>>
Represents an N-dimensional interval (hyperrectangle) over Real numbers.

This is a convenience wrapper around FieldIntervalND for Real numbers, providing backward-compatible API with List-based access.

An N-dimensional interval is the Cartesian product of N 1-dimensional intervals: [a₁,b₁] × [a₂,b₂] × ... × [aₙ,bₙ]

Since:
2.0
Author:
Silvere Martin-Michiellot, Gemini AI (Google DeepMind)
